# User System with Google OAuth, Shared Shopping Lists & Invitations

The current Weekly Shopping List app has no user system — all data is global. This plan introduces Google OAuth authentication (backend-side, cookie-based), multi-list ownership, invitations/subscriptions, and per-user item history.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Google OAuth Setup**: You'll need to create (or already have) a Google Cloud OAuth 2.0 Client ID and Client Secret. These will be added as `GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID` and `GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET` in [.env.local](file:///d:/code/weekly-shopping-list/.env.local). The OAuth redirect URI must be configured in Google Cloud Console to point to your app's callback (e.g., `http://localhost:3000/api/auth/google/callback` for dev, and your production URL).

> [!WARNING]
> **Data Migration**: Existing items, history, and categories in the database are currently "ownerless". The plan creates a migration script to assign all existing data to your user (`jordi8284@gmail.com`) as the initial owner. This should be run once after deployment.

> [!CAUTION]
> **Breaking Change**: After this change, unauthenticated users cannot access any data. The app will redirect to a login page for all protected routes and API calls.

